clear. GBP/JPY spent the bulk of mid-to-late June grinding through a congestion band centred around the 212.50\u2013213.80 area, repeatedly finding buyers at the prior reaction zone near 213.33 \u2014 a level that attracted five separate touches and held each time. That persistent defence of structure eventually gave way to a meaningful directional leg. The 29th of June marked the inflection point, with a decisive daily close above 214.70 triggering a sequence of higher closes that carried the pair through 215.57 \u2014 itself a prior reaction zone that had capped price on three occasions \u2014 and then onward through the 216 handle. The 6th of July delivered the breakout candle, a near two-figure advance that cleared the range with conviction. Since then, the pair has been consolidating those gains in a relatively tight band between roughly 216.40 and 218.05, with each dip finding willing buyers rather than sustained sellers. The prior reaction zone at 215.57 now sits well below current price and represents the first meaningful structural reference should the market retrace.\n\nThe hourly picture reinforces the constructive read. Price spent the Asian and early European hours oscillating in a narrow corridor just above 217.00, never threatening a meaningful breakdown. From the London afternoon onwards, the hourly candles stepped progressively higher \u2014 a sequence of higher lows and higher highs through the 15:00 to 22:00 window \u2014 culminating in the current print near the session high. There is no obvious distribution pattern on the H1; the late-session push to 217.79 looks like continuation rather than exhaustion, though the pace of advance has moderated into the close.\n\nThe calendar is empty today, which removes the risk of sharp data-driven dislocations in either direction. That absence of scheduled event risk tends to favour the prevailing momentum, with price action more likely to reflect positioning and technical flows rather than fundamental repricing. It also means any volatility that does emerge would carry greater significance as a signal of organic order flow.\n\nThe bullish read would come under pressure on a daily close back below the 216.40 area, which has acted as a floor across several sessions since the breakout. A sustained move beneath 215.57 \u2014 the former resistance now treated as structure support \u2014 would represent a more material challenge to the current thesis and would warrant reassessment of the near-term directional picture.\n\nThis is editorial analysis, not financial advice. Trading involves substantial risk of loss.", "sample": false}